  "body": "**Is this a BUG REPORT or FEATURE REQUEST?**:\r\n/kind bug\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\n\r\nIn https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/issues/54637#issuecomment-344584988 we found that Horizontal Pod Autoscaler test fails on large clusters, despite its deployment under test is tiny (1-2 nodes). The conclusion was that the reason is most likely that heapster fails to scrape metrics from thousands of nodes in a timely manner (the test does pass on large scale, but very rarely).\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\n\r\nRun a gce-large-correctness job (2k nodes).\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know?**:\r\n\r\nInterestingly, on 2k GKE cluster the HPA tests pass: https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/issues/54637#issuecomment-344587938",
